',0,1,0,0,'2015-11-18 00:57:37','2015-11-18 00:57:37',21,55,65),(474,'Incorrect','If 0.10 M acetic acid had minimal effect on the pH when mixed with 0.010 M hydrochloric acid, then a weak acid with a smaller dissociation constant will have even less effect (i.e., virtually none).',0,0,1,0,'2015-11-18 00:57:37','2015-11-18 00:57:37',21,54,66),(475,'Background: Calcium Carbonate','Calcium carbonate is a mineral that covers 4% of the Earth\'s crust. It is mined and quarried and has numerous industrial and commercial applications.',1,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 18:42:33','2015-11-23 18:46:13',22,NULL,1),(476,'Background: Calcium Carbonate','For example, one of the main uses of calcium carbonate is the manufacture of cement and concrete, as well as other construction materials.\n\nMany famous buildings and statues are made from calcium carbonate in the form of marble or limestone.',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 18:59:03','2015-11-23 19:36:31',22,NULL,2),(477,'Background: Calcium Carbonate','Calcium carbonate is used as a filler material for pharmaceuticals, an antacid, and as a dietary calcium supplement.',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 19:02:16','2015-11-23 19:39:10',22,NULL,3),(478,'Background: Calcium Carbonate','Calcium carbonate is also used as filler, white pigment, and opacifier in the production of paper.',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 19:05:09','2016-01-29 01:10:09',22,NULL,4),(479,'Background: Calcium Carbonate','In addition, calcium carbonate is a biologically important structural material, being a main component of the shells of conchs, urchins, clams, oysters, scallops, crabs, and lobsters.',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 19:06:22','2016-01-29 01:10:22',22,NULL,5),(480,'Scenario','Atmospheric carbon dioxide dissolves in water to form carbonic acid.\n\nMany natural bodies of water sit on rock, soil or sediments that contain calcium carbonate.',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 19:13:35','2015-11-23 19:51:19',22,NULL,6),(481,'Carbonic Acid','What type of acid is carbonic acid?',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 19:41:36','2015-11-23 20:04:03',22,NULL,7),(482,'Title','What species are weak acids?',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 19:42:55','2015-11-23 20:08:54',22,NULL,8),(483,'',NULL,0,0,1,0,'2015-11-23 19:53:02','2015-11-23 20:05:58',22,60,9),(484,'Title','What species is amphoteric?',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 20:09:39','2015-11-23 20:11:33',22,NULL,10),(485,'Title','Calcium carbonate is a sparingly soluble solid. What equilibrium constant(s) will determine its solubility?',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 20:12:29','2015-11-23 20:17:27',22,NULL,11),(486,'Title','Is carbonate an acid, base, or neither?',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 20:14:57','2015-11-23 20:21:18',22,NULL,12),(487,'','Given that the autoionization of water is always applicable. \n\nWhat other equilibrium constants will apply?',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 20:17:27','2015-11-23 20:32:44',22,NULL,13),(488,'Title','What equilibrium constants apply to the basic behavior of carbonate?\n\n(Not including autoionization of water.)',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-23 20:23:11','2015-11-23 20:30:20',22,NULL,14),(489,'',NULL,0,0,0,0,'2015-11-24 21:56:39','2015-11-24 21:56:53',22,NULL,15),(490,'Begin','You are just beginning your research on Cordacae, a subject you know nothing about. Where do you begin?',1,0,0,0,'2015-11-25 18:20:44','2015-12-14 06:13:26',23,NULL,1),(491,'Summon','Summon is an excellent starting point for your research and has many tools to help you make your search fast, efficient and targeted at scholarly sources....\nWhere would you like to go instead?',0,0,0,0,'2015-11-25 18:21:19','2015-12-14 06:18:28',23,NULL,2),(492,'Syllabus1','What are you looking for in your syllabus?',0,0,0,0,'2015-12-14 06:14:09','2015-12-14 06:19:03',23,NULL,3),(493,'Google','Google is a great tool to help introduce you to basic concepts, vocabulary, and current opinions on your topic.\nDo you want to use any Advanced Search options for this Google search?',0,0,0,0,'2015-12-14 06:14:12','2015-12-14 06:32:39',23,NULL,4),(494,'Assignment1','Where would you like to begin your research for this paper?',0,0,0,0,'201